<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-450-074  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 450 074.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Software  July 1989 v6 n4 p113(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Comparing the accuracy of Fortran math libraries. (SoftwareReview)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miller, Tom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An evaluation and comparison of four mathematical-functionlibraries that are included with three common FORTRAN compilersfor the MSDOS environment revealed excellent accuracy and minimalerrors in the included functions.andP;  Lahey Fortran F77L 2.2,Ryan-McFarland RM-Fortran 2.4, and Microsoft Fortran OptimizingCompiler 4.0 all offer math-function libraries for Intel 8087 and80387 math coprocessors, while Microsoft also offers an alternateseries of math routines.andP;  The math functions of each library weretested for errors due to rounding and fixed-length representationof real numbers.andP;  Single- and double-precision approximations fora variety of often used functions were tested with programswritten for each function.andP;  2,000 random arguments distributedover primary intervals were used to test the accuracy of eachfunction.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     FORTRANMathematical ProgrammingEvaluationComparisonFunction AnalysisError AnalysisFunctionsLibraries.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Worst-case results for elementary functions' loss of bits. (table)Comparing the Microsoft i87 library against the Microsoftalternate library. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>